## Section 2: Implementation Status Rules

### Never Claim "Ready for Implementation"

**What AI Can Say:**
- ‚úÖ "Documentation completed"
- ‚úÖ "Requirements defined"
- ‚úÖ "Analysis finished"
- ‚úÖ "Design documented"
- ‚úÖ "Specifications prepared"
- ‚úÖ "Architecture documented"
- ‚úÖ "Technical design complete"

**What AI Cannot Say (Without Explicit User Confirmation):**
- ‚ùå "Status: Ready for Implementation"
- ‚ùå "Next Step: Begin implementation"
- ‚ùå "Implementation Priority: High"
- ‚ùå "Ready to start core functionality"
- ‚ùå "All blockers cleared - ready to proceed"

### When Status Indicators Are Allowed

**ONLY use status indicators when:**
- ‚úÖ User explicitly tells you the status
- ‚úÖ User provides specific status information
- ‚úÖ User confirms readiness
- ‚úÖ User gives explicit permission

### Rationale: Technical vs Business Readiness

**Technical Readiness (AI can confirm):**
- ‚úÖ Requirements documented
- ‚úÖ Design completed
- ‚úÖ Architecture documented

**Business Readiness (Only humans can approve):**
- Stakeholder approval
- Budget allocation
- Resource availability
- Timeline confirmation
- Priority ranking

**AI can confirm technical documentation is complete. Only humans can approve implementation.**

